description:
&lt;p&gt;10 North are seeking Band 5 Staff Nurses to join our awarding team in Acute Medicine for Elderly People.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Acute Medicine for Elderly People wards at the Royal Free Hospital employs over 100 staff across two wards. We have the full support of the Trust in our continued journey to be leaders in excellent nursing care for elderly patients, the senior management team proactively share our values and vision. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for nursing staff that have an interest in working in this complex, specialised and rewarding area of nursing. We want nurses who are compassionate, bright and motivated to deliver the best care for this wonderful group of patients. The 10 North team are hardworking and passionate about their roles and we value the importance of teamwork. The ward teams are supported by the Ward Sister, a Practice Educator, Dementia OT, Matron, and dedicated &amp; supportive Consultants.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to develop your clinical knowledge and skills and to be part of a nursing team that is leading the way in elderly care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We support flexible working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eduarda Rodrigues Ward Manager - 10 North on 0207 794 0500 ext 34014 or via email eduarda.rodrigues@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
